Privacy Policy for Dark Mode Toggle

Last updated: 08/03/20204

Introduction
Thank you for using the Dark Mode Toggle Chrome extension. Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding your data.

Information We Collect
Dark Mode Toggle does not collect, store, or transmit any personal information from users. The extension operates entirely on your device and does not communicate with external servers or services.

How We Use Information
Active Tab and Scripting Permissions: These permissions are solely used to apply the dark mode styling to the current webpage. The extension modifies the appearance of web pages by injecting CSS directly into the active tab. No data is sent or received from your device.
Data Sharing and Disclosure
Since we do not collect or store any data, there is no information to share or disclose with third parties.

Security
We are committed to keeping your information secure. As the extension does not collect personal data, there are no data storage or transmission concerns. The extension is designed to operate solely within your browser environment.

Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and the date of the latest update will be indicated at the top of the policy. We encourage you to review this policy periodically for any changes.

Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at befhobby@gmail.com. 
